;&quot;Identity&quot;
:When &quot;t&quot; = &quot;t&quot;0, &quot;U&quot; is the identity operator, since formula_19
;&quot;Closure&quot;
:Time evolution from &quot;t&quot;0 to &quot;t&quot; may be viewed as a two-step time evolution, first from &quot;t&quot;0 to an intermediate time &quot;t&quot;1, and then from &quot;t&quot;1 to the final time &quot;t&quot;. Therefore, formula_20

